        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/editor_top_basic.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Every time you click one of the lower tabs, your input is saved, but you can also click <guibutton>Save</guibutton> to save the record.</para>
        <para>When you have finished editing, click the <guibutton>Save and Close</guibutton> button. The record is saved inside the folder you marked before opening the editor and the record you have just added is displayed in the search interface.</para>
        <para>After you have closed the editor, you can at any time reopen the record inside the editor by clicking the <guibutton>Edit Record</guibutton> button &#160;<graphic fileref="../../../resources/images/page_edit.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160; inside the detail view of the record.</para>
        <para>If you wish to discard whatever you have input and want to return to the search function, click <guibutton>Cancel Editing</guibutton>.</para>
